Nico Heyns, who was a pilot for Working on Fire, died earlier this week. CAPE TOWN - A memorial service will be held on Sunday in honour of a helicopter pilot who died while battling a wildfire along the Garden Route. Nico Heyns, who was a pilot for Working on Fire, died earlier this week. The 65-year-old’s chopper had crashed during firefighting efforts in Vermaaklikheid on Tuesday. Kishugu aviation's chairperson Trevor Abrahams says: “Working on Fire will be joining the Nico Heyns’ family, friends and colleagues for a celebration of his life on Sunday at a farm in Knysna. The family requested that this be a private event.” An investigation into the cause of the incident is currently ongoing. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)